===Noun===
'''episcopus''', '''episcopi''', ''m''; second declension noun

# [[bishop]]; an official in a Christian church who rules or governs a region of the church sometimes called a [[diocese]], or a similar official in other religions.  An overseer or supervisor.

====Etymology====
From Greek [[episkopos]], from ''epi-'', '''upon''' or '''over''' + ''skopos'', '''sight'''.

